
'''= Circle is a membership-based service open to anyone over the age of 50, supporting individuals and communities to lead the lives they want to lead.'''

URL = http://www.southwarkcircle.org.uk/


=Description=

"Southwark Circle employs local people called Neighbourhood Helpers to help out with a variety of tasks. Some are great at DIY, other like teaching how to do things like use the Internet or speak a language, and of course there are some with "green fingers" to help out with gardening. All Neighbourhood Helpers are background checked and live locally. So getting help through Southwark Circle means you're getting things done and helping out the community at the same time."
(http://www.southwarkcircle.org.uk/getting_things_done.php)



